	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Altough I don't know if XPCMK is "evolved and optimized" enough or not.</div>
<br />
<br />It's fairly evolved, but I don't know about optimized. In particular, the player code uses up more ROM space than it would need.
<br />
<br />Feature-wise, some of the things that are missing are
<br />
<br />* Portamentos. You can of course do them manually with EP just like with p(p)mck, but it'd be nice to have them handled automatically.
<br />* Virtual sound registers. The playback libraries currently writes directly to the sound chip(s).
<br />
<br />But it does add a few things like patterns (to save space in compiled music data) and callbacks (let's you trigger a function to be called on the host CPU from your song, once or every time a new note is played).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


