<br />
<br />Improvising extra metatiles rows isn't wrong either. If I prot my game to the C64 I'll have to do the opposite : Remove some metatiles rows (and possibly improvise columns).
<br />
<br />About XPMCK, does it use that "1 note = 1 byte" format, or does it so 1 note = 2 bytes like the oly MCK ? Does it support for sound effects, or if not could it be added easily into the project ? I guess I'd PM you because you know I love sound engine, and I've always wanted to make (or bring my contribution) to one who is multi-platform. Seems there is no NES version (because of PPMCK ?). But while PPMCK is nice and "elvolved", it waste ROM space (because 1 note = 2 bytes), the tempo is done at compiling and not at runtime, and the comments are in japanese  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" />

		

